{
  "title": "Observing Microservices using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer demonstrates how to leverage FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+, to observe microservices in your application.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI simplifies the process of creating APIs and offers built-in features like OpenAPI support and automatic JSON serialization.",
    "In this example, we'll use FastAPI to create an API endpoint for observing a microservice.",
    "Python 3.12+ is required as it includes improvements to the type hints feature that FastAPI utilizes.",
    "For this example, we will be using the Uvicorn ASGI server as the production-ready server for running FastAPI applications."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/healthcheck')\ndef healthcheck():\n    return {'status': 'OK'}\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='0.0.0.0', port=8000)"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "FastAPI version: 0.69.0",
    "Python version: 3.12.0"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure that you have the required dependencies installed, including FastAPI, Uvicorn, and type-var.",
    "Run `pip install fastapi uvicorn type-var` to install the necessary packages."
  ]
}
